HEADWORD: Malambo
<hw>Ma*lam"bo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg.]</ety>
<def>A yellowish aromatic bark, used in medicine and perfumery, said to
be from the South American shrub <spn>Croton Malambo</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

